uientry.unicode: Displays resource production in this province for your faction.
Indicates the amount of gold that can be mined in this region. Once depleted the region will provide only 10% of its normal produciton.
This is the amount of income this province generates every turn.
Indicates province population, public order and influence

Once [[img:icon_growth]][[/img]]growth reaches a certain threshold, [[img:icon_pop_surplus]][[/img]]population surplus is created. This can then be spent on upgrading your settlement building, which will open an additional building slot.||{{tr:click_to_open_hp}}

state.unicode: Under control||The population is either happy, or too scared of you to do anything!||Although both will keep order in your province, a happy population will increase town growth.
Neutral||The population are neither unhappy nor completely under your control.||You may wish to take steps to improve your control over them, such as increasing repression.
Unhappy||The population is unhappy and could easily riot and rebel.||Increase repression in this area to keep things from getting worse.

uientry.unicode: Any transitory effects that apply to this province will appear here. These may come from various sources including [[img:icon_hero]][[/img]]agent actions and random events.||{{tr:click_to_open_hp}}
